                <h2>Why Some Patients Fail: When Does Microneedling NOT Work?</h2>

                <p>It is medically irresponsible to claim a 100% universal success rate. When patients aggressively complain in forums demanding to know <strong>does microneedling work</strong> because their specific face saw absolutely zero improvement, the failure is almost always heavily categorized into three very specific clinical errors:</p>

                <h3>1. Inadequate Penetration Depth</h3>
                <p>If you have heavily scarred cheeks featuring deep 2.0mm boxcar depressions, and you go to a cheap, unverified salon that uses a terrifying plastic roller stamped with 0.5mm needles, it is an absolute biological guarantee that the treatment will fiercely fail. A 0.5mm needle physically cannot reach heavily into the dense lower dermis to cut the rigid scar anchors. Depth calibration by a certified medical doctor like Dr. Nyra is the single highest defining factor of success. Read closely about <a href="is-microneedling-safe.php">is microneedling safe when done strictly at home</a> to heavily understand this terrifying failure point.</p>

                <h3>2. Lack of Patience and Session Continuation</h3>
                <p>Collagen is not a quick-dry cement. It takes the human biological system anywhere from 4 to 6 weeks to fully synthesize, heavily pack, and structurally remodel strong Type-I collagen following a severe micro-injury event. If a patient does exactly one session, looks in the mirror two weeks later, and angrily declares the treatment a catastrophic failure, they lack basic anatomical education. Massive facial reconstruction requires a highly disciplined commitment to 4 to 6 consecutive clinical sessions.</p>

                <h3>3. Severe Internal Protein Deficiencies</h3>
                <p>Collagen is an incredibly complex protein structure heavily demanding intense nutritional building blocks (specifically massive Vitamin C, Zinc, and amino acids). If you are clinically malnourished, aggressively vegan strictly lacking heavy protein, or completely devoid of dietary Vitamin C, your body simply lacks the raw biological bricks necessary to build the new wall. We heavily advise exploring exactly <a href="what-to-eat-for-hair-growth.php">what to eat for cellular regeneration</a> before undergoing thousands of heavy needle punctures.</p>

